  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Overview&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This tool mentor supports Designing Subsystems with Rational XDE Developer - Java Platform Edition.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The steps in this tool mentor match those in the corresponding task.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Links to topics in XDE online Help are marked with &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The following steps are performed in this tool mentor:&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a href=&quot;#Distribute%20Subsystem%20behavior&quot;>Distribute Subsystem Behavior to Subsystem Elements&lt;/a>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a href=&quot;#Document%20Subsystem%20Elements&quot;>Document Subsystem Elements&lt;/a>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a href=&quot;#Describe%20Subsystem%20Dependencies&quot;>Describe Subsystem Dependencies&lt;/a>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Distribute Subsystem behavior&quot; name=&quot;Distribute Subsystem behavior&quot;>&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>Distribute Subsystem Behavior&#xD;
    to Subsystem Elements&lt;/font>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Classes and other subsystems are added within the subsystem to realize the subsystem interfaces.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The collaborations of model elements within the subsystem must be documented using sequence diagrams that show how the&#xD;
    subsystem behavior is realized. Each operation on an interface that is realized by the subsystem must have one or more&#xD;
    documented sequence diagrams. This diagram, which is owned by the subsystem, is used to design the internal behavior of&#xD;
    the subsystem.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create class diagrams as needed. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding&#xD;
        Diagrams&lt;/i> &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_dgm&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add subsystems and classes. See &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/toolmentors/identifying_design_elements_F8D68BA1.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{E6727D13-BE7B-4025-AD39-ECD6FA074D73}&quot;>Tool Mentor: Identifying Design Elements Using Rational XDE&lt;/a> for&#xD;
        guidance on adding new subsystems and classes.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Document how each interface operation is realized, as follows: &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Add a collaboration instance for each interface operation. Name it after the operation. (In the Model&#xD;
                Explorer, right-click the subsystem package, and then click &lt;b>Add UML&lt;/b> &lt;b>&amp;gt; Collaboration&#xD;
                Instance&lt;/b>.)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Create an interaction instance with the same name. (In the Model Explorer, right-click the collaboration&#xD;
                instance, and then click &lt;b>Add UML&lt;/b> &lt;b>&amp;gt; Collaboration Instance&lt;/b>.)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Create a sequence diagram for this interaction instance. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot;&#xD;
                src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Diagrams&lt;/i> &#xD;
                &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_dgm&quot;); -->.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Drag and drop classes and interfaces onto the diagram to create objects for interaction. See &lt;img&#xD;
                alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Shapes to Diagrams&lt;/i> &#xD;
                &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_shp_dgm&quot;); -->.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Add messages or stimuli between objects. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot;&#xD;
                src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Messages or Stimuli&lt;/i> &#xD;
                &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_messages&quot;); -->.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Assign operations to messages. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot;&#xD;
                src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Assigning Operations to Messages or Stimuli&lt;/i> &#xD;
                &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_assgn_op_mess&quot;); -->.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For more information, refer to the following topics in the Rational XDE online Help:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Working with Class Diagrams&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_o_work_w_class_dgms&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Working with Interaction (Sequence) Diagrams&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_o_work_inter_dgm&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Modeling Java and Web Applications&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;j&quot;,&quot;j_o_java_mdling&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Document Subsystem Elements&quot; name=&quot;Document Subsystem Elements&quot;>&lt;b>&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>Document Subsystem&#xD;
    Elements&lt;/font>&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Reference: &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Documenting Model Elements&lt;/i> &#xD;
    &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_doc_model_elem&quot;); -->&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Describe Subsystem Dependencies&quot; name=&quot;Describe Subsystem Dependencies&quot;>&lt;b>&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>Describe Subsystem&#xD;
    Dependencies&lt;/font>&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    When an element contained in a subsystem uses some behavior of an element contained in another subsystem, a dependency&#xD;
    is created between the enclosing subsystems. To improve reuse and reduce maintenance dependencies, express this&#xD;
    situation in terms of a dependency on a particular interface of the subsystem, not upon the subsystem itself nor upon&#xD;
    the element contained in the subsystem.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Reference: &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Dependency Relationships&lt;/i> &#xD;
    &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_depend_relshp&quot;); -->&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
